  sodium: 3 g
  serving size: 684
course: main course
---

Peel and chop the @onion{1/2} into roughly 1cm pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Chop the @closed cup mushrooms{1} into roughly 1cm pieces. Separate the @broccoli{1} into florets and peel and chop the @sweet potato{1/2} and @potato{1/2} into roughly 2cm cubes.

Bring a #large pot{} of water to the boil with a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and preheat your #oven{} to 220 degrees. Put a #large saucepan{} on medium heat with a glug of @oil{glug} and add your onion. Cook for ~{4%mins} until soft and then add your garlic and mushrooms. Cook for ~{3%mins} then add the @British beef mince{250%g} along with a pinch of salt and a good grind of @black pepper{good grind}. Cook your beef for about ~{4-5%mins} or until browned. Break it up with a #spoon{} as it cooks.

Meanwhile, add your potatoes to the boiling water and cook for ~{15-20%mins}.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

Once they are cooked, drain them, put them back in the pot and add the @Netherend butter salted{15%g} and a splash of @?milk{splash} (if you have some), along with a pinch of salt and a good grind of black pepper. Mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}.

When your beef has browned, add the @tomato puree{1}, @chopped tomatoes{1/2}, @Worcester sauce{1/2} and the @beef stock pot{1/2}. Bring to the boil, then reduce to a simmer and cook for ~{15%mins} to thicken.

When your beef has been cooking for 15 mins, transfer it to an #ovenproof dish{}, spread your mash on top, then grate over the @mature Cheddar cheese{30%g}. Pop your dish on the top shelf of your oven for ~{15-20%mins}.

Put your broccoli onto a #baking tray{}, sprinkle over a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of black pepper along with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. When your cottage pie has been in your oven for ~{5%mins}, put your broccoli on the middle shelf for ~{10-15%mins}.

When your cottage pie is bubbling and golden brown, get it out of your oven and serve on plates with your roasted broccoli on the side.